26#include "config.h"
27#include "NetworkCacheCoders.h"
28
29namespace WTF {
30namespace Persistence {
31
32// Store common HTTP headers as strings instead of using their value in the HTTPHeaderName enumeration
33// so that the headers stored in the cache stays valid even after HTTPHeaderName.in gets updated.
34void Coder<WebCore::HTTPHeaderMap>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const WebCore::HTTPHeaderMap& headers)
35{
36 encoder << static_cast<uint64_t>(headers.size());
37 for (auto& keyValue : headers) {
38 encoder << keyValue.key;
39 encoder << keyValue.value;
40 }
41}
42
43std::optional<WebCore::HTTPHeaderMap> Coder<WebCore::HTTPHeaderMap>::decode(Decoder& decoder)
44{
45 std::optional<uint64_t> headersSize;
46 decoder >> headersSize;
47 if (!headersSize)
48 return std::nullopt;
49
50 WebCore::HTTPHeaderMap headers;
51 for (uint64_t i = 0; i < *headersSize; ++i) {
52 std::optional<String> name;
53 decoder >> name;
54 if (!name)
55 return std::nullopt;
56 std::optional<String> value;
57 decoder >> value;
58 if (!value)
59 return std::nullopt;
60 headers.append(WTFMove(*name), WTFMove(*value));
61 }
62 return headers;
63}

65}
